The day we arrived in Antarctica was one that I will never forget. The weather was crisp but clear and the visibility was exceptional. 

The glaciated mountains and jagged, rock-like chunks of ice overlooking the placid bay were as picture-perfect as it gets. 

Max had reached his final continent and became the youngest American to visit all seven continents. 

It didn’t really sink in until that night when we were at dinner and I felt a huge sense of accomplishment. If we could set this record, what other records could we set? The world is full of possibilities, and the more unrealistic you are with your dreams and goals, the more you are able to achieve.

I’ve talked a lot over the years about travel essentials. One thing I can’t leave home without is a great pair of sunglasses. I’ve always been sensitive to light and it’s only gotten worse as I get older. Actually, I had an eye accident in January and I’ve been struggling with eye issues ever since. 

I found a company with great styles, but it’s their mission that I can really get behind. 

Ecoer is on a mission to help save the Ocean from Plastic Pollution and save Marine Life.

We recently embarked on a 24-hour escapade at Stonebriar Centre in Frisco, Texas. 

Our adventure began with a check-in at the Hyatt Regency Frisco. The hotel's central location was perfect for our busy schedule. Directly attached to Stonebriar Centre, shopping entertainment, dining, and a library are all just a few steps away. 

We strolled through a myriad of shops, each offering a unique treasure trove. Window shopping is lovely this time of year with all festive decor. 

The aroma of sizzling pizza dough and bubbling cheese beckoned us inside Smokin' Oak Wood-Fired Pizza & Taproom, and, to our surprise, it was karaoke night. We enjoyed belting out a few tunes while enjoying our food and drinks. 

After dinner, we opted for an exciting evening at AMC DINE-IN Stonebriar 24. Reclining in the plush seats, we enjoyed a cinematic masterpiece while eating popcorn. It was the perfect blend of comfort and entertainment. 

The thrill continued the next morning as we delved into the Back in Time Escape Rooms.

Then, we enjoyed lunch in the Food Court before heading to KidZania. Athena and her friends tried their hands at various professions, from modeling to news broadcasting, unleashing their creativity and imaginations. It was a joy to see them immerse themselves in the make-believe world, reminding me of the limitless possibilities of childhood.

For a touch of serenity, we visited Library CONNECTION, a haven for book lovers. While the girls explored the variety of books, I discovered a cozy nook to continue reading my captivating novel. It was a tranquil pause amidst the hustle and bustle, a moment to appreciate the importance of balancing excitement with quiet reflection.

We finished our day at Dave & Buster's. From classic arcade games to immersive virtual reality experiences, the laughter and friendly competition echoed through the neon-lit venue.

As the 24-hour clock wound down, I couldn't help but marvel at the myriad experiences packed into our whirlwind journey.
